item.written_book.1.page.0.1:
The Legend of Gerald:

Gerald was a young frog from a middle class suburban family. He didn't know much, besides what society told him; that frogs just had to be frogs. Yet Gerald wanted more. He knew there was more out there for him, so he dared to dream.
item.written_book.1.page.1.1: The very next day, he took a leap of faith by deciding that frogs didn't need to walk on four legs, in fact, they only needed two. So he leaned back, and he ran. He ran faster than any frog had before. He ran past everything he had ever known, past his mother and father, past his brother and
item.written_book.1.page.2.1:
sister, right out the front door of their house, into the open road.
  As Gerald began to reach the sound barrier his eyes welled with tears. "This was it," he thought, "this is my destiny."
  Gerald's two legs continued to push him onward, and he continued to speed up.
item.written_book.1.page.3.1: At this point, Gerald knew he couldn't turn back, no one in his town would want to see him again. He was a monster, a speed demon, a frog that suddenly had a craving for chili dogs and golden rings. Gerald knew he had no other choice but to keep running, and so he ran.
item.written_book.1.page.4.1:
FIVE YEARS LATER
  It's been a long time since anyone has last seen Gerald. His parents have passed on, and his siblings have grown old and had tadpoles of their own.
  The story of Gerald's feat of incredible speed has become the stuff of legend in this town, as
item.written_book.1.page.5.1: many a troubled young frog have tried to replicate the stunt, though none were able. One could only wonder if Gerald ever felt that his dream was fulfilled, with his controversial theory of two-legged frogs being scoffed at by most modern frog scientists. Who knows where he is today, but
item.written_book.1.page.6.1:
perhaps he can rest easy knowing that his story has been told.     Now, dear reader, you can carry on the legacy of Gerald, the fastest frog to ever live.




Based on a true story
    - By Calverin

command_storage.book_storage.SavedItem.t: This book allows you to apply basic settings to an armor stand. Clicking the coloured links will adjust the closest armor stand within three blocks.

Turn gravity off before nudging the Y-position.

Relative Aligned nudging moves the armor stand relative to the player's position and aligned to the block grid.  (X=Left/Right, Z=Away/Towards)

Relative Aligned nudging moves the armor stand relative to the player's exact position.  (X=Left/Right, Y=Above/Below, Z=Away/Towards)

Nudges are in 16ths of a block to align with the pixels of the block textures.

The angle step (default 15°) is used for both the stand rotation and the pose adjustments.

Toward and Away turn the armor stand to face toward or away from you.
Points selected appendage at head or feet.

The Death pose is for a figure lying down and requires a separate armor stand for the legs.

Randomized creates a completely unique randomized custom pose.

The Block and Item presets are designed to hold blocks and items in line with the world grid.
The angle step set for adjusting the stand rotation is also used for the pose adjustments.
Pose and position an armor stand to align a held block or item with an adjacent block.
Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that a block held by it appears on the surface.
Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that an item held by it appears upright on the surface.
Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that a non-tool item held by it appears flat on the surface.
Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that a tool held by it appears flat on the surface.

Align an armor stand with a tripwire hook on the wall above it so that a tool held by it appears to be hanging up.

Also locks the armor stand and disables all slots except the mainhand.
Mirroring copies the arm or leg pose from left to right or vice versa. Flipping reverses the armor stand's pose entirely.

Copying an armor stand stores it's settings and pose in the book and these can then be pasted into another armor stand. The book must be the selected item in your mainhand or offhand for this to work.

Locking an armor stand prevents it from being changed using the book and disables interaction with the equipment slots.

Sealing an armor stand, which is only available in creative mode, does the same and in addition makes it invulnerable

If two of these statistics hit zero, you will begin to die.
scenario.functions.play_dodgeball.telepo: Dodge shulker bullets until time runs out.
scenario.functions.play_dodgeball.tutori: Shulkers will shoot shulker bullets towards you from above.
Run around within the bounds of the white circle to avoid being hit.
scenario.functions.play_gene_says.genera: Get away from the living room!
scenario.functions.play_gene_says.telepo: Follow Gene's instructions. Disobey his instructions if it isn't preceded by: "Gene says."
scenario.functions.play_gene_says.tutori: You will receive instructions on your screen.
If "Gene says" is not preceding an action, don't follow it.
If you fail to finish an instruction or complete an incorrect action, you will fail.
Survive ten rounds to win the scenario.
scenario.functions.play_the_piano.get_pa: Drop a block to play notes on the piano!
scenario.functions.play_the_piano.start_: Repeat the notes you saw by dropping the items in your inventory. You will have 15 seconds for each individual note.
scenario.functions.play_the_piano.telepo: Repeat the notes played for you on the piano.
scenario.functions.play_the_piano.tutori: A note will appear on the piano.
After it has played, you will have a short time to drop that note from your inventory.
The sequence will then have one note added, and this process repeats until there are six notes.
If you misplay a note, you will lose.
Repeat the six-note melody to win the scenario.
scenario.functions.repel_a_nether_invasi: Kill fifteen mobs and return to a beacon.
You must kill fifteen mobs from the Nether.
The mobs will become stronger over time.
Use your three golden apples and three healing potions to help stay alive.
If you die, you join the enemy team and can help kill other players.
Otherwise, once you have fifteen kills, escape through one of the tunnels (found near the beacons) to win!
scenario.functions.rescue_royalty.telepo: Kill a knight to obtain their key and then secure the top of the tower.
scenario.functions.rescue_royalty.tutori: The royal-person is inside the top of the tower.
Hold the paper in your inventory to see a particle trail pointing to the tower.
The entrances to the tower's top are locked.
Three knights spawn somewhere near the castle.
They will drop the key on death.
Many other mobs are guarding the area.
Every mob kill will give you health, resistance, and strength for a short time.
Reach and secure the top of the tower before time runs out and before dying to win the scenario.
scenario.functions.scale_a_storm.telepor: Use tridents to go through the checkered circle right under the cloud.
scenario.functions.scale_a_storm.tutoria: Use riptide tridents to climb the storm.
Go through the checkered circle at the top before time runs out to beat the scenario.
scenario.functions.skydive.teleport.2: Survive five random dropper levels in a row.
scenario.functions.skydive.tutorial.5: Jump out of the plane and avoid taking fall damage using things like water, slime blocks, scaffolding, and more.
scenario.functions.skydive.tutorial.7: You must complete five randomized levels with each level increasing in difficulty.
scenario.functions.skydive.tutorial.9: You must complete all five levels in a row without dying.
scenario.functions.skydive.warning_1.1: Jump out of the plane within
scenario.functions.steal_a_gem.active.2: Keep this weapon concealed when possible!
scenario.functions.steal_a_gem.active.4: Right-click the gem with an empty hand!
scenario.functions.steal_a_gem.active.15: Alright that's enough gems, get in the van and let's go!
The carrier of the gem has fallen. Pick up the gem and get to the truck!
scenario.functions.steal_a_gem.start.8: Make this quick! I have 1:30 left on this song then I'm leaving without y'all.
Subtly get to the vault or loot the offices, take the gems, and get back to your truck.
Avoid holding your sword near guards.
Don't get too close to any patrolling guards.
If guards become too suspicious of you, they will attack. You can see their suspicion level in the boss bar.
Loot offices and cubicles for enough smaller gems to win.
Alternatively, reach the elevator in the back to go to the vault and take the largest, most valuable gem.
Once the vault is open, the alarm will trigger, and the guards will become aggressive.
Once you have enough smaller gems or the largest gem from the vault, get back to the truck before the driver leaves without you.
Enter the back of the truck to drop off smaller gems and contribute towards the required amount, or the largest gem to reach the amount immediately.
Once the required amount is reached, any player who enters the back of the truck before time runs out will win.
scenario.functions.steal_a_gem_old.activ: Keep this weapon concealed when possible.
Loot up then get to the elevator at the back of the bank.
Run to the vault and grab the gem inside.
Get to the elevator at the back of the bank.
Escort the gem to the truck.
scenario.functions.steal_a_gem_old.telep: Loot up, get to the vault, take the gem, and get to your truck.
scenario.functions.steal_a_gem_old.tutor: If guards become too suspicious of you, they will attack. You can check the suspicion level in the boss bar.
Loot offices and cubicles for items.
After getting loot, reach the elevator in the back to go to the vault.
Take the gem from the vault. Once the vault is open, the alarm will trigger, and the guards will become aggressive.
Get back upstairs and follow the particle tracker to your truck.
The back of the truck will open soon after the gem is near it.
Once the gem is in the truck, any player who reaches it before time runs out will win.
scenario.functions.stop_a_robot_uprising: You have died! You now have
You have died! You have lost.
Time is up! The robots have survived.
All mobs and players are one-tap.
When you die, you will respawn outside the factory.
You have a limited number of lives, which will appear on your action bar.
There are several types of enemy robots. Some will destroy nearby arrows, explode near players, or shoot at you.
The archer robot gives off a warning particle around itself.
Your goal is to kill the three glowing "commander" robots before time runs out or you run out of lives.
scenario.functions.survive_a_ghast_a.tel: Evade fire and fireballs from ghasts until time runs out.
scenario.functions.survive_a_ghast_a.tut: Ghasts appear on all sides and move back and forth.
They shoot fireballs, which will light pillars on fire underneath them.
Make sure to listen for their screech. It is a warning before the ghast shoots.
Jump between the pillars and survive until the timer reaches zero.
scenario.functions.survive_in_the_wilder: Drop on the campfire to extend the flame!
Keep your statistics (Warmth, Hunger, and Thirst) above zero until time runs out.
You have three statistics, "Warmth," "Hunger," and "Thirst." They appear in your action bar and will all slowly diminish as you play.
Sticks appear randomly across the ground. Drop them on the campfire to extend the flame.
You can see how much time the campfire has before extinguishing on the boss bar.
If you lose your campfire, your statistics will start dropping faster.
Water appears in two of the map's corners. You can find other items around the map to either help your statistics fall slower or boost them.
You succeed once the timer reaches zero.
scenario.functions.walk_a_tightrope.tuto: Walk and jump across the iron bars..
Falling will cause you to die.
Reach the end of the parkour course before time runs out to beat the scenario.
scenario.functions.work_in_an_anvil_fact: Dodge falling anvils until the timer runs out.
Anvils will come crashing down from above.
Run around and survive until the timer runs out.
